Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka IV: Shin Shou Meikyuu-hen

The fourth season of Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka. Intrepid adventurer Bell Cranel has leveled up, but he cant rest on his dungeoneering laurels just yet. The Hestia Familia still has a long way to go before it can stand toe-to-toe with the other Familias of Orario but before Bell can set out on his next mission, reports of a brutal murder rock the adventuring community! One of Bells trusted allies stands accused of the horrible crime, and its up to Bell and his friends to clear their name and uncover a nefarious plot brewing in the dungeons dark depths. (Source: Sentai Filmworks)
Comedy, Drama, Romance, Slice of Life

"What am I doing?" Yuuhi Nagi's high school life is already halfway over, but he still doesn't have any dreams, ambitions, or even friends in his class! Every day is boring, until he's suddenly in danger of getting held back! A bittersweet high school drama made up of 4 potential grade repeaters with the worst grades in the class and 1 student acting as their teacher!
(Source: Pocket Comics)
Makenshi no Maken Niyoru Maken no Tame no Harem Life

Just an ordinary high school student, Fujinomiya Sojiros life was cut short when he was stabbed by a burglar one fateful night. Or so he thought. Revived by a mysterious deity, Sojiro finds himself transported to another world, armed with a legendary samurai sword, Hotomaru, plus the very blade that ended his life. Whats more, Sojiro discovers that these enchanted blades can transform into beautiful babes! As Sojiro embarks on a thrilling adventure full of magic and danger, he will need to build a harem of steel in order to survive this strange new world.
(Source: Seven Seas Entertainment)
